A '''business necessity''' is a legitimate [[business]] purpose that justifies an employment decision as effective and needed to optimally achieve the organization’s goals and ensure that operations run safely and efficiently.<ref>Cascio, W. F., & Aguinis, H. (2010). Applied Psychology in Human Resource Management,  Prentice Hall.</ref> This is often presented as a defense of an employment decision that is questioned because it was found to cause [[disparate impact]].

