A '''performance supervision system''' ('''PSS''') is a [[software system]] used to improve the performance of a [[Industrial process|process]] [[Factory|plant]]. Typical process plants include [[oil refineries]], [[paper mills]], and [[chemical plant]]s.
The PSS gathers real-time data from the [[process control]] system, typically a [[distributed control system]]. Using this data, the PSS can calculate performance [[Metric (mathematics)|metrics]] for process equipment, controls, and operations.
